-- Polish Central Bank Sees Zloty, Rate Risk Due to Budget in 2011 Guidelines
-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 2010-09-30T14:06:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/polish-central-bank-sees-zloty-rate-risk-due-to-budget-in-2011-guidelines.html
Poland’s fiscal deficit will
probably remain at a “very high level” next year, posing the
risk of a more volatile zloty and higher long-term interest
rates if a public-debt limit set at 55 percent of gross domestic
product is breached, the central bank said in Monetary Policy
Guidelines for 2011 published today on its website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
